title._content: Eight Hour Procession. 4th October, 1909, With compliments from "The Star".

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales
tag.author: 29454428@N08

description._content: Reproduced in 'The Star: The Australian Evening Daily' newspaper, Monday Oct 4, 1909, p.4. This Labour Day procession demanded an eight-hour working day. The basic principle of the eight hour movement was to divide the day into three eight hour periods - eight hours work, eight hours recreation and eight hours sleep. The banners often featured three intertwined 8s.
